2. Definitions

"Software" means the source code, binaries, and documentation in this
repository, and any modified versions of them.

"Official Service" means the dosya.dev cloud storage service operated by
dosya.dev and reachable at dosya.dev and its subdomains.

"Contribution" means any work you intentionally submit for inclusion in the
Software (for example, a pull request to this repository).

3. What you may do

  a. Read and audit. You may view, download, and study the source code for
     any purpose.

  b. Build and run. You may compile, install, and run the Software,
     unmodified or with your own patches, for your personal use or your
     organization's internal use, but only in connection with the Official
     Service.

  c. Contribute. You may fork this repository on GitHub and modify the
     Software for the sole purpose of developing and submitting
     Contributions back to this repository.

4. What you may not do

  a. Redistribute. You may not distribute, publish, sell, rent, lease, or
     sublicense the Software or modified versions of it. Maintaining a
     public fork on GitHub for the purpose of submitting Contributions is
     allowed.

  b. Use other backends. You may not use, adapt, or configure the Software
     to connect to, interoperate with, or provide any service other than
     the Official Service.

  c. Compete. You may not use the Software, in whole or in part, to provide
     a hosted, managed, or commercial service, or to build a product or
     service that competes with the Official Service.

  d. Remove notices. You may not remove or obscure copyright, license, or
     attribution notices.

